race.comment: MONEY ON MY MIND (11) resumed a month ago for the new yard with a narrow defeat at Gatton. She has trialled well since at Ipswich and keeps the 1.5kg claim. The former Sydney galloper can go one better over the longer sprint. BUTWEDID (1) resumed with a satisfactory effort over 1200m at Sunshine Coast. Has a solid second-up record and is well placed at country level. Has a wide gate but can make the finish with average luck. KAMIGAMO (10) is a former Victorian who needed the outing at the Sunshine Coast first up. Maps well and has a 2kg claim. Strips fitter and can improve into the finish. THE RAIN KING (6) draws wide but creates interest on debut for the Robe yard. Has trialled well and has the blinkers on signalling intent. CLAW MACHINE (2) will go better over this trip and can get some of the money on his best figures.
